cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper is about neural information retrieval (IR) models and their effectiveness in improving ad hoc retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques in IR, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of different neural models, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper applies these models to image retrieval, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
